[[File:Clam_Lake_ELF.jpg|thumb]]
'''極低頻'''（'''E'''xtremely '''L'''ow '''F'''requency，'''ELF'''）<ref>{{cite web|url=http://terms.naer.edu.tw/detail/2367394/|title=極低頻率，超低頻|work=國家教育研究院|accessdate=2019-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403104449/http://terms.naer.edu.tw/detail/2367394/|archive-date=2019-04-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref>是指[[頻率|頻率]]由3Hz至30Hz<ref name="ITU Nomenclature">{{cite web |title=Rec. ITU-R V.431-7, Nomenclature of the frequency and wavelength bands used in telecommunications |url=http://www.itu.int/dms_pubrec/itu-r/rec/v/R-REC-V.431-7-200005-I!!PDF-E.pdf |publisher=ITU |accessdate=20 February 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031020427/http://www.itu.int/dms_pubrec/itu-r/rec/v/R-REC-V.431-7-200005-I%21%21PDF-E.pdf |archivedate=31 October 2013}}</ref>，[[波長|波長]]10,000公里至100,000公里的[[無線電波|無線電波]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nasa.gov/directorates/heo/scan/communications/outreach/funfacts/txt_band_designators_prt.htm |publisher=NASA |title=Extremely Low Frequency |work=ANL Glossary |accessdate=28 September 2013 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304211614/http://www.nasa.gov/directorates/heo/scan/communications/outreach/funfacts/txt_band_designators_prt.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.solareis.anl.gov/glossacro/dsp_wordpopup.cfm?word_id=4668 |title=Extremely low frequency |work=ANL Glossary |accessdate=9 August 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029202624/http://www.solareis.anl.gov/glossacro/dsp_wordpopup.cfm?word_id=4668 |archive-date=2013-10-29 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 。

極低頻無線電波是[[閃電|閃電]]和自然擾動在[[地球磁場|地球磁場]]中產生的，因此是[[大氣科學|大氣科學]]中研究的主題之一。由於難以製造可以輻射這種長波的[[天線|天線]]，因此極低頻無線電波極少用於[[通信|通信]]系統中。ELF波可以穿透[[海水|海水]]，這使它們可以用於與[[潛艇|潛艇]]的通信。[[美國|美國]]、[[俄羅斯|俄羅斯]]、[[印度|印度]]和[[中華人民共和國|中華人民共和國]]是目前僅有已知建造ELF通信設施的國家。<ref name="NavyFactSheet">{{cite web |title=Extremely Low Frequency Transmitter Site, Clam Lake, Wisconsin |work=Navy Fact File |publisher=United States Navy |date=28 June 2001 |url=http://www.fas.org/nuke/guide/usa/c3i/fs_clam_lake_elf2003.pdf |format= |doi= |accessdate=17 February 2012 |archive-date=2021-01-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125180942/https://fas.org/nuke/guide/usa/c3i/fs_clam_lake_elf2003.pdf |dead-url=no }} at the [http://www.fas.org/ Federation of American Scientists website] {{Wayback|url=http://www.fas.org/ |date=20110217023057 }}</ref><ref name="Wolkoff">{{cite conference |first=E. A. |last=Wolkoff |author2=W. A. Kraimer |title=Pattern Measurements of U.S. Navy ELF Antennas |booktitle=ELF/VLF/LF Radio Propagation and Systems Aspects |pages=26.1–26.10 |publisher=AGARD Conference proceedings 28 Sept. – 2 Oct. 1992, NATO |date=May 1993 |location=Belgium |url=http://www.dtic.mil/dtic/tr/fulltext/u2/a267991.pdf |doi= |id= |accessdate=17 February 2012 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303222529/http://www.dtic.mil/dtic/tr/fulltext/u2/a267991.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Coe">{{cite book |last=Coe |first=Lewis |title=Wireless Radio: A brief history |publisher=McFarland |year=2006 |location=USA |pages=143–144 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=W1JAeg1PiWIC&pg=PA143&dq=%22extremely+low+frequency%22+ELF+propagation+waveguide#v=onepage&q=%22extremely%20low%20frequency%22%20ELF%20propagation%20waveguide&f=false |doi= |id= |isbn=978-0786426621}}</ref><ref name="Sterling">{{cite book |last=Sterling |first=Christopher H. |title=Military communications: from ancient times to the 21st century |publisher=ABC-CLIO |year=2008 |location= |pages=431–432 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=RBC2nY1rp5MC&printsec=frontcover#v=snippet&q=zevs&f=false |doi= |id= |isbn=978-1851097326}}</ref><ref name="Bashkuev">{{cite journal |last=Bashkuev |first=Yu. B. |author2=V. B. Khaptanov |author3=A. V. Khankharaev |title=Analysis of Propagation Conditions of ELF Radio Waves on the "Zeus"–Transbaikalia Path |journal=Radiophysics and Quantum Electronics |volume=46 |issue=12 |pages=909–917 |date=December 2003 |issn= |doi=10.1023/B:RAQE.0000029585.02723.11 |id= |bibcode = 2003R&QE...46..909B }}</ref><ref name="Trond">{{cite web |last=Jacobsen |first=Trond |title=ZEVS, The Russian 82 Hz ELF Transmitter |work=Radio Waves Below 22 kHz |publisher=Renato Romero webpage |year=2001 |url=http://www.vlf.it/zevs/zevs.htm |doi= |accessdate=17 February 2012 |archive-date=2011-07-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110709075829/http://www.vlf.it/zevs/zevs.htm |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="janes">{{cite web |last1=Hardy |first1=James |title=India makes headway with ELF site construction |url=http://www.janes.com/article/11147/india-makes-headway-with-elf-site-construction |publisher=[[Jane's_Information_Group|IHS Jane's Defence Weekly]] |accessdate=23 February 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223135343/http://www.janes.com/article/11147/india-makes-headway-with-elf-site-construction |archivedate=23 February 2014 |date=28 February 2013}}</ref><ref name="toi14">{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Navy-gets-new-facility-to-communicate-with-nuclear-submarines-prowling-underwater/articleshow/39371121.cms |title=Navy gets new facility to communicate with nuclear submarines prowling underwater |date=31 July 2014 |work=[[The_Times_of_India|The Times of India]] |access-date=2019-04-03 |archive-date=2021-02-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225192454/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Navy-gets-new-facility-to-communicate-with-nuclear-submarines-prowling-underwater/articleshow/39371121.cms |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==應用==
基於無線電於[[鹹水|鹹水]]的傳送特性，除了極低頻和[[超低頻|超低頻]]外，通常無線電波不容易在海中傳送。雖然它可以在水中容易地傳送，但是ELF每分鐘可以傳送的訊號相對地小，所以只是給[[美軍|美軍]]用作指示潛水艇進入或離開海底。另外要有效傳送極低頻信號需要大型的[[天線|天線]]，所以極低頻的使用不太普遍。

一些國家的[[電氣化鐵路|電氣化鐵路]]使用低於一般50/60 Hz[[工頻|工頻]]的極低頻[[交流電|交流電]]，例如[[德國|德國]]、[[奧地利|奧地利]]、[[瑞士|瑞士]]、[[挪威|挪威]]和[[瑞典|瑞典]]使用15,000V 16.67Hz，美國使用11,000V或12,500V 25Hz的交流電。

